@startuml secuencia-mtls
!theme plain
title Experimento 02 - Diagrama de Secuencia: Handshake mTLS Istio vs Linkerd

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #EAF4FB
skinparam participantBorderColor #2980B9

actor "Cliente" as C
participant "Ingress Gateway" as GW

box "Configuracion Istio mTLS STRICT" #D6EAF8
  participant "Envoy Sidecar\n(api-service)" as SA
  participant "api-service" as API
  participant "Envoy Sidecar\n(auth-service)" as SB
  participant "auth-service" as AUTH
end box

box "Control Plane" #FDFEFE
  participant "istiod\n(Istio CA)" as ISTIOD
end box

== Inicializacion: Istiod emite certificados SPIFFE ==

ISTIOD -> SA : Certificado SPIFFE\nspiffe://cluster.local/ns/realistic-istio-mtls/sa/api
ISTIOD -> SB : Certificado SPIFFE\nspiffe://cluster.local/ns/realistic-istio-mtls/sa/auth

== Peticion del cliente ==

C -> GW : HTTPS POST /login\n{credentials}
GW -> SA : TCP Proxied

== Handshake mTLS entre api-service y auth-service ==

SA -> SB : TLS ClientHello\n+ certificado SPIFFE de SA

note over SA, SB
  Ambos sidecars verifican:
  1. Certificado valido y no expirado
  2. Firmado por la CA de confianza (istiod)
  3. SPIFFE URI pertenece al mismo trust domain
end note

SB -> SA : TLS ServerHello\n+ certificado SPIFFE de SB\n+ ServerFinished
SA -> SB : ClientFinished\n(Canal mTLS establecido)
SA --> API : peticion via localhost\n(sin overhead TLS adicional)
API -> AUTH : peticion via localhost\n(sidecar maneja mTLS)
AUTH --> SB : respuesta
SB --> SA : respuesta via mTLS
SA --> GW : respuesta
GW --> C : HTTPS 200 {jwt_token}

== Intento de conexion HTTP plano (rechazado por STRICT) ==

participant "Servicio\nExterno" as EXT

EXT -> SB : HTTP plano (sin TLS)
SB -> SB : Verificar PeerAuthentication\nmode: STRICT
SB --> EXT : Connection Reset / 503\n(HTTP plano RECHAZADO)

note over EXT, SB
  PeerAuthentication mode: STRICT
  Rechaza cualquier conexion que no
  presente un certificado mTLS valido
end note

== Linkerd: mTLS Automatico (sin configuracion) ==

box "Configuracion Linkerd" #F9EBEA
  participant "Linkerd Proxy\n(api-service)" as LA
  participant "api-service\n(Linkerd)" as LAPI
  participant "Linkerd Proxy\n(auth-service)" as LB
  participant "auth-service\n(Linkerd)" as LAUTH
end box

C -> LA : HTTP (Nginx termina HTTPS)
LA -> LA : Detectar destino de red
LA -> LB : mTLS automatico\n(certificados gestionados por Linkerd)
LB --> LA : Respuesta via mTLS
LA --> LAPI : localhost
LAPI -> LAUTH : via proxy Linkerd
LAUTH --> LAPI : respuesta
LAPI --> C : respuesta final

note over LA, LB
  Linkerd gestiona mTLS automaticamente:
  - Sin PeerAuthentication manual
  - Sin DestinationRule
  - Certificados rotados cada 24h
  - Proxy mas liviano (Rust vs C++ Envoy)
end note

@enduml
